[Claude]: Now I have enough information to submit all the findings. The core vulnerability is clear:

1. `ResourceHelper.resolveResourceAsInputStream()` directly opens a `FileInputStream` when URI starts with `file:` with no path validation
2. HTTP input (request body/headers) flows to this method through multiple code paths
3. An attacker can inject `file:///etc/passwd` or `file:/../../../etc/passwd` to read arbitrary files

